<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up next to a flat bench. Grasp a pair of suitable dumbbells from the weight rack and place one on either side of the bench. Sit at the front of the bench with the dumbbells next to you.</li>



<li>Reach down to pick up the dumbbells. Maintain a neutral back position with your chest up.</li>



<li>Bring your torso forward until it&#8217;s at a 45-degree angle. Your head should be facing down with your arms by your sides.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and bring the dumbbells outward while maintaining a slight elbow bend. Your torso should stay in the same position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position.</li>



<li>Inhale and lower the dumbbells back to the starting position under control.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core engaged to maintain a neutral back position. This helps to reduce possible lower back strain.</li>



<li>Ensure your head is looking down at the same position throughout. This prevents potential neck strain.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



