</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Set up an adjustable bench so the backrest is at the top position. Grasp a suitable dumbbell from the weight rack using a neutral grip. Both hands should be at the top of the dumbbell next to the dumbbell head.</li>



<li>Sit on the weight bench with your back against the backrest. Bring the dumbbell above and behind your head. The dumbbell should be at head height with your elbows tucked next to your ears.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core. Exhale and extend your elbows to bring the dumbbell up.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause briefly at the top position.</li>



<li>Inhale and bring the dumbbell back to the starting position under control.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips </h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your elbows tucked in as you extend your elbows. This ensures targeted muscle focus.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Your feet should stay firmly against the ground throughout each repetition. This provides a stable lifting base.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



